name: Adam Harris
about: Adam Harris is a professional multi-asset market analyst and content partner specializing in high-quality technical and macro commentary for brokers, trading platforms, and financial media. He produces structured written and video analysis covering Forex, commodities, indices, equities, and cryptocurrencies, focusing on clarity, neutrality, and educational value for newer and intermediate traders. His work includes weekly multi-market analysis, platform-specific content, live webinars, and educational pieces published through partners and media outlets. He currently contributes written and video content to Investing.com and provides analysis and commentary to several global brokers and trading communities. He prioritizes professionalism, accuracy, and long-term partnership value, delivering content that supports client engagement.
business_context: Chief Market Analyst | Professional Financial Markets Commentator | Multi-Asset Technical Analyst | Content & Webinar Partner to Brokers and Trading Platforms | Writer for Investing.com

name: Charlie Arwood
about: Charlie Arwood is a Forex Trader at Veritas Hedge Fund. He has experience trading commodities, equities, options, and is currently focused mainly on Forex, specifically GBP/JPY. His personal trading style includes a day trading strategy aiming to make 75 pips a day, with 25 pips profit locked in and letting the other position "ride" for 50 pips profit. He uses a combination of technical and fundamental analysis with a particular view from "the other side of the chart" (market manipulation). His goal is to get about 2 to 4 opportunities per week, finishing his work week before Friday. He began trading after being inspired by Ken Robert's "The World's Most Powerful Money Manual" brochure and has studied and discovered his trading approach over years.
business_context: Forex Trader at Veritas Hedge Fund
